I think that means you lose the debate when you get so upset that you cease to make sense. <br>
<br>
No one is attacking you, not anymore than you meant to attack us. You don't seem to have any ability to see what you said, and how it made be construed as non-support. You jumped on a tangent, over a point of DBC's post that you read incorrectly, and then you made a very broad, unsupportable statement, which you were called on. Some of us gave extreme examples to make a point. I don't think a single person on here ever said you shouldn't have kids because you work.  Your choice is to work, and for good reasons, but without saying &quot;For me, I've done both, and for me, it is less stressful to be home&quot;....you came across as belittling.<br>
<br>
I think what the vast majority of us have said has been crystalline. It's tough to be a parent, WOH or SAH. You have to do what works for you, and what works for your family. But you shouldn't stand up, and villify the other side to make yourself feel better, which is how you came across. I support WOH moms and dads, and the SAHP, on the presumption that they have found what works for them.<br>
