I don't mean to be sexist with my comments about my husband. He just is absolutely useless when it comes to infants. As DS gets older he is starting to do more and more with him, but I don't think he willingly held Edison the first 2 months of his life. Infants terrify him. Now he should have worked at getting over it, but that's neither here nor there. But frankly, he is the better parent (normally) of our toddler. He and she work out disagreements better. I think he compromises way too much with her, but I don't interfer with him and her and he doesn't interfer with me and her. I also think he probably believes I'm too unmovable at times. Of course I am also the one here all day every day. An almost three year old is hard at times. Especially one like Laurel.<br>
