DH is also perfectly capable of cleaning and picking up. He just doesn't. And when he does pick up he won't put things into their right place. They just go into what every shelf, box, etc that is closest. And DH can't cook. His mother never taught him. And he moved in with me two weeks after leaving his mother's house. Ohh mistake on my part. Should have made him work on his own for a while. <br>
<br>
Thisisn't the example I grew up with. My Dad was very much an active part of house hold chores and child raising - well less of the child raising, his temper would never have suited him to be a long term sahd. Even now, my dad cooks easily 75% of my parents dinners. If I need cooking advice (more often then I like to admit) all but for one meal, I call Dad and ask him. Actually, a lot of house hold questions I call Dad and ask him. He's talked me through fixing my lawnmower, installing a perminate babygate, fixing a broken faucet, getting grease stains out of clothing. So its very frustrating that DH does so little. And I do worry about hte example it is setting for my children. <br>
