Why would a woman, pregnant and facing divorce CHOOSE to continue the pregnancy and put the child in the dreaded daycare to support it? Would you prefer she abort? Or must she give the child up for adoption? If not, why is daycare okay for her child?<br>
<br>
What if she was widowed? Must she abort or give up her deceased husband's child rather than put it in daycare? What if she gives it up for adoption, and the adoptive mother chooses to return to work and the child ends up in daycare anyway?<br>
<br>
What about kids a woman already has when she ends up single for whatever reason (death, divorce)? Should they be farmed out to SAHP's rather than be put in daycare?<br>
<br>
Edited to add: What if her husband is simply demoted at work and can no longer support the family on his income alone? If the mother must return to work, should they put the kids up for adoption to avoid the trauma of daycare?<br>
