 <p>&quot;Beware of a clear and present evil in the name of some future, nebulous good.&quot;</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=doublelatte>Double Latte</A> at: 5/5/03 10:44:04 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#9fb7df><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=powertotherae>Powertotherae</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Satan's Lil' Minion</span><br>  Posts: 270<br> <font color=#3333ff>(5/5/03 11:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=196.topic&index=57>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Back to the question...</span><hr size=1> Ok I will bite (Maude help me). First I want to say that this isn’t a judgment, I am not talking about anybody on this board, and I am not trying to offend. This is only my personal experience. So please don’t go insane and eat me alive!! Feel sorry for me I am pregnant (can I use that?<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br>
<br>
When I said the comment what is the point of having kids. To be honest I really don’t know. I am an all or nothing person so for me if I couldn’t SH then I wouldn’t have kids. So I honestly cannot understand what the purpose of having children would be for me if I couldn’t be there all the time. I also don’t want to share the joy of my children with anyone (except of course my dh).<br>
<br>
My worst fear in life is that I will die and my kids will end up in daycare. I honestly don’t know why. So I guess I am a hater of daycare. Maybe its because I have been a SAHM this whole time and haven’t had any experience with daycare. All I hear are my friend’s horror stories and that is what sticks in my mind.<br>
<br>
The distinction I made about someone choosing to go back to work didn’t come out right. I personally have friends who had kids because that is what they are supposed to do but really don’t want to be involved. So they couldn’t wait to put their kids in daycare so they could get their life back. To me that is annoying. I have friends who don’t work but have full time nannies so they don’t have to be tied down. That is where I was coming from with my comment. And yes to me I see no point in having kids if you don’t even enjoy them. <br>
<br>
Does this clarify at all where I am coming from? I have been thinking about this for days trying to figure out a way to explain where I am coming from without making it seem that I think people who put their kids in daycare are bad parents.<br>
<br>
<br>
Leah <p>&quot;It ain't the parts of the Bible that I can't understand that bother me, it is the parts that I do understand.&quot; <br>
Mark Twain </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#b9a1d0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> sweetpeas mommy</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#3333ff>(5/5/03 11:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=196.topic&index=58>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  why have kids</span><hr size=1> Leah, you said, &quot; personally have friends who had kids because that is what they are supposed to do but really don’t want to be involved. So they couldn’t wait to put their kids in daycare so they could get their life back. To me that is annoying. I have friends who don’t work but have full time nannies so they don’t have to be tied down. That is where I was coming from with my comment. And yes to me I see no point in having kids if you don’t even enjoy them.&quot;<br>
<br>
I know people like that as well and it IS annoying. The worst example is that my dh used to work with this woman who expressed shock that I would ~choose~ to stay home with our dd and said in her opinion, women who stayed home were drains on society and when she had kids, she put them in daycare as soon as possible because she wanted to be &quot;productive&quot;. She didn't seem to like her children very much and even said that she had had them because she was in &quot;that part of life.&quot; I don't know what her husband's feelings about having children were.<br>
<br>
Now I certainly don't advocate abortion, but, in my opinion, I do wonder why she had kids. Not why she continued her pregnancies, but why she chose to go off birth control and get pregnant in the first place. (Yes, I know BC fails sometimes but in this case, she chose to get pregnant..she said as much.) <br>
<br>
I'm not a &quot;daycare-hater&quot;...I have many friends who work and have their kids in good daycare situations and everybody is happy and well-adjusted. My own dd goes to daycare at the local YMCA a couple mornings a week while I work out. And it's been a great experience for her because she is learning to socialize and interact with other children. She loves it.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I am starting to ramble now, and I think I need to go change a diaper....there's a suspicious smell coming from the general vicinity of my dd and her toybox! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
